prvtRsvp.name: prvtRsvp

revisions.description: Added range constraints to prvtRsvpProductLocalRepairDelay, prvtRsvpProductRefreshInterval, prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRInterval, prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRLimit, prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRInterval, prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRLimit.

prvtRsvp.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtRsvp.description: The MIB module for management of the PRVT-RSVP product.

PrvtRsvpAdminStatus.name: PrvtRsvpAdminStatus
PrvtRsvpAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative state of an RSVP entity.

PrvtRsvpOperStatus.name: PrvtRsvpOperStatus
PrvtRsvpOperStatus.description: The current operational state of an RSVP entity.

PrvtRsvpIndex.name: PrvtRsvpIndex
PrvtRsvpIndex.description: The index value identifying an RSVP entity.

PrvtRsvpDiagReqIndex.name: PrvtRsvpDiagReqIndex
PrvtRsvpDiagReqIndex.description: The index value identifying an RSVP session that is being diagnosed.

PrvtRsvpDiagNodeIndexType.name: PrvtRsvpDiagNodeIndexType
PrvtRsvpDiagNodeIndexType.description: The index value identifying a node within an RSVP session that is being diagnosed.

PrvtRsvpDiagNodeTypeVal.name: PrvtRsvpDiagNodeTypeVal
PrvtRsvpDiagNodeTypeVal.description: The type of a node in a session that is being diagnosed.

prvtRsvpProductEntry.name: prvtRsvpProductEntry
prvtRsvpProductEntry.description: Each entry represents an RSVP entity.

prvtRsvpProductIndex.name: prvtRsvpProductIndex
prvtRsvpProductIndex.description: The index of this prvtRsvpProductEntry. This is the HAF entity index passed on the entity create parameters.

prvtRsvpProductASNumber.name: prvtRsvpProductASNumber
prvtRsvpProductASNumber.description: The number identifying the autonomous system (AS) to which this node belongs.

prvtRsvpProductSenderTTL.name: prvtRsvpProductSenderTTL
prvtRsvpProductSenderTTL.description: The TTL set on messages originating at this node. A value of 0 indicates this number is determined by other means.

prvtRsvpProductMinTimerPeriod.name: prvtRsvpProductMinTimerPeriod
prvtRsvpProductMinTimerPeriod.description: The minimum granularity to allow an internal timer to be set in the PRVT-RSVP product code.

prvtRsvpProductAPIIfIndex.name: prvtRsvpProductAPIIfIndex
prvtRsvpProductAPIIfIndex.description: Management assigned interface identifier for the (internal) LRAPI interface between RSVP and TE-MIB components. This must be unique in the interface index namespace of the node - it MUST not match any real interface index. It is recommended that this is set to zero or 0x7FFFFFFF.

prvtRsvpProductAPIAddress.name: prvtRsvpProductAPIAddress
prvtRsvpProductAPIAddress.description: Management assigned IP address used to identify the (internal) LRAPI interface between RSVP and TE-MIB components. The configured API address MUST not be a real address in the network. It is recommended that this is set to a non-zero reserved address value, such as 224.0.0.0. If multi-stack support is set to PHOP, this address must be unique for each RSVP stack in the node. The same address(es) can be used on all nodes in the network.

prvtRsvpProductLocalRepairDelay.name: prvtRsvpProductLocalRepairDelay
prvtRsvpProductLocalRepairDelay.description: This object is used to set the delay between detection of a path error and instigation of local repair procedures. This allows local routing updates to converge. A value of -1 indicates that local repair procedures should not take place, but that the error should be propagated upstream. Where FRR capabilities are supported at this node local_repair_delay must be set to -1.

prvtRsvpProductRefreshInterval.name: prvtRsvpProductRefreshInterval
prvtRsvpProductRefreshInterval.description: This RSVP value, R, which is used to set the average interval between refresh path and resv messages. Note : If values for the if_refresh_interval and if_refresh_multiple are configured such that the following inequality is not obeyed : 6 * refresh_interval * (refresh_multiple + 0.5) < 0x7FFFFFFF. Then the time-to-die for the path value will be set to its maximum value and it is probable that the lsp will time out before a refresh arrives.

prvtRsvpProductRefreshMultiple.name: prvtRsvpProductRefreshMultiple
prvtRsvpProductRefreshMultiple.description: The RSVP value, K, which is the number of unresponded Path or Resv refresh attempts which must be made, spaced by the refresh interval before the state is deemed to have timed out. Note : See note in prvtRsvpProductRefreshInterval above.

prvtRsvpProductRfrshSlewDenom.name: prvtRsvpProductRfrshSlewDenom
prvtRsvpProductRfrshSlewDenom.description: The denominator of the fraction, SlewMax, which is the maximum allowable increase in the refresh interval, R, to prevent state timeout while changing R. R is increased by this fraction until it reaches the new desired value.

prvtRsvpProductRfrshSlewNumerator.name: prvtRsvpProductRfrshSlewNumerator
prvtRsvpProductRfrshSlewNumerator.description: The numerator of the fraction, SlewMax, which is the maximum allowable increase in the refresh interval, R, to prevent state timeout while changing R. R is increased by this fraction until it reaches the new desired value.

prvtRsvpProductBlockadeMultiple.name: prvtRsvpProductBlockadeMultiple
prvtRsvpProductBlockadeMultiple.description: The RSVP value, Kb, which is the number of refresh timeout periods after which blockade state is deleted.

prvtRsvpProductSocketBufPoolSize.name: prvtRsvpProductSocketBufPoolSize
prvtRsvpProductSocketBufPoolSize.description: The number of pre-reserved buffers available for sending sockets data. This is used to pace the sockets data flows.

prvtRsvpProductSwitchBufPoolSize.name: prvtRsvpProductSwitchBufPoolSize
prvtRsvpProductSwitchBufPoolSize.description: The number of pre-reserved buffers available for programming the switch. This is used to ensure programming operations do not fail in buffer shortage conditions.

prvtRsvpProductTeMibBufPoolSize.name: prvtRsvpProductTeMibBufPoolSize
prvtRsvpProductTeMibBufPoolSize.description: The number of pre-reserved buffers available for signalling TE-MIB. This is used to ensure signals are not lost in buffer shortage conditions.

prvtRsvpProductRoutingBufPoolSize.name: prvtRsvpProductRoutingBufPoolSize
prvtRsvpProductRoutingBufPoolSize.description: The number of pre-reserved buffers available for route queries. This is used to ensure re-routing of many LSPs does not fail in buffer shortage conditions.

prvtRsvpProductLSPSetupPriority.name: prvtRsvpProductLSPSetupPriority
prvtRsvpProductLSPSetupPriority.description: The setup priority to apply to LSPs which are not signalling this parameter. 0 represents the highest priority, 7 the lowest. The value of this object must be numerically more or equal (so lower or equal priority) than the value of the holding priority object.

prvtRsvpProductLSPHoldingPriority.name: prvtRsvpProductLSPHoldingPriority
prvtRsvpProductLSPHoldingPriority.description: The holding priority to apply to LSPs which are not signalling this parameter. 0 represents the highest priority, 7 the lowest. The value of this object must be numerically less or equal (so higher or equal priority) than the value of the holding priority object.

prvtRsvpProductAdminStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductAdminStatus
prvtRsvpProductAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative state of the RSVP entity.

prvtRsvpProductOperStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductOperStatus
prvtRsvpProductOperStatus.description: The current operational state of this instance of PRVT-RSVP.

prvtRsvpProductRowStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductRowStatus
prvtRsvpProductRowStatus.description: Used to create and delete a PRVT-RSVP Product Table entry. When this object is set to 'active', only the prvtRsvpProductAdminStatus object in the row may be modified.

prvtRsvpProductLsrIndex.name: prvtRsvpProductLsrIndex
prvtRsvpProductLsrIndex.description: The index of the PRVT-LMGR product instance which this PRVT-RSVP is to join to as its LDB interface provider. If this value is not specified, or the value of this object is 0, PRVT-RSVP will use the prvtRsvpProductIndex value as the Lsr index when joining on the LDB interface.

prvtRsvpProductTeMibIndex.name: prvtRsvpProductTeMibIndex
prvtRsvpProductTeMibIndex.description: The index of the TE-MIB product instance which this PRVT-RSVP is to join to as its LRA interface provider. If this value is not specified, or the value of this object is 0, PRVT-RSVP will use the prvtRsvpProductIndex value as the TeMib Index when joining on the LRA interface.

prvtRsvpProductMultiStackSupport.name: prvtRsvpProductMultiStackSupport
prvtRsvpProductMultiStackSupport.description: A flag to indicate if multiple RSVP stacks are present in the same system as the current one and, if so, how they are supported. If set to PHOP, Path messages are forwarded to PRVT-RSVP with the Previous Hop value set as the hop prior to the incoming interface, not as the next hop interface as normal. If set to LIH, the hardware location of the current RSVP stack is used as the LIH in the HOP object.

prvtRsvpProductUseHopByHop.name: prvtRsvpProductUseHopByHop
prvtRsvpProductUseHopByHop.description: A flag to indicate that PRVT-RSVP should use the hop by hop addressing scheme for PATH and PATH-TEAR messages it sends. If set then the IP addresses used in the IP header of PATH messages forwarded by PRVT-RSVP set source as the local outgoing interface IP address, and destination as the next hop router IP address.

prvtRsvpProductUseNotify.name: prvtRsvpProductUseNotify
prvtRsvpProductUseNotify.description: A flag to indicate that PRVT-RSVP should attempt to insert a Notify Request object in all Path requests that is sends as ingress and all Resv requests that it sends as egress. The precise behavior is modified by a user exit called by the RSVP code. This field is not used unless the mplsTunnelUpNotRecip or mplsTunnelDownNotRecip fields in TE-MIB are set to 0.0.0.0.

prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRDecay.name: prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRDecay
prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRDecay.description: The percentage increase in the rapid retransmission interval for each consecutive unacknowledged RSVP Notify message. A value of 0 indicates a constant retransmission rate.

prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRInterval.name: prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRInterval
prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRInterval.description: The interval in milliseconds before a Notify message is first resent if no acknowledgement is received.

prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRLimit.name: prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRLimit
prvtRsvpProductNotifyRRLimit.description: The maximum number of times a Notify message is resent if no acknowledgement is received.

prvtRsvpProductAllowIPEncap.name: prvtRsvpProductAllowIPEncap
prvtRsvpProductAllowIPEncap.description: A flag to indicate that PRVT-RSVP should support the use of IP encapsulation of RSVP packets, which are required for out-of-band signaling. If set, then PRVT-RSVP will accept incoming RSVP packets that are IP encapsulated, and will IP encapsulate outgoing packets whenever the IP routing stub indicates that it is required for a particular route.

prvtRsvpProductProtocolExtensions.name: prvtRsvpProductProtocolExtensions
prvtRsvpProductProtocolExtensions.description: Specifies which extensions to the standard RSVP-TE protocol are enabled. For fully standards-compliant behavior, set this parameter to zero (no bits set). To enable specific non-standard protocol extensions, set this parameter to the bitwise OR of whichever of the following behaviors you wish to enable. - bypassFastReroute: Enable support for facility fast reroute protection of LSPs (bypass LSP protection). This flag is deprecated in favour of the prvtRsvpProductFrrFacAdminStatus field which can be modified while RSVP is admin up, however either field can be used. When this flag is set RSVP automatically sets the prvtRsvpProductFrrFacAdminStatus. - detourFastReroute: Enable support for one-to-one fast reroute protection of LSPs (detour LSP protection). - noResAffOnInIf: Disable resource affinity checking on incoming interfaces for LSPs. If this flag is set, RSVP will accept Path messages which use invalid resource affinities for the incoming interface used by the LSP.

prvtRsvpProductPSRFlags.name: prvtRsvpProductPSRFlags
prvtRsvpProductPSRFlags.description: This field is used by PRVT-RSVP to determine whether it should set the Path State Removed flag on a PathErr (and therefore remove corresponding state and generate a PathTear). Each bit of this flags field corresponds to a situation where PRVT-RSVP may generate a PathErr. Setting a particular bit will result in PRVT-RSVP removing state, setting the Path State Removed flag and generating a PathTear in that corresponding situation. The possible bit values are - pathErrPSRSet: PRVT-RSVP has received a PathErr message with the Path State Removed flag set. - pathErrPSRNotSet: PRVT-RSVP has received a PathErr message with the Path State Removed flag unset. - ldbCommonRcvd: PRVT-RSVP has received a negative response to an ATG_LDB_RESERVE_LSP_XC or ATG_LDB_CONNECT_LSP_XC message. - ldbPreempted: PRVT-RSVP has received a Preemption message from Label Manager. - routingError: PRVT-RSVP has received a Negative response to an ATG_IPR_QUERY_ROUTE message. - invalidPathMsg: PRVT-RSVP has received an invalid Path message. - sessionExpired: A session in PRVT-RSVP has expired. - unableToRepairRoute: A route has been removed and PRVT-RSVP is unable to start local repair. - unableToRepairIf: An interface has been removed and PRVT-RSVP is unable start local repair. - reachedRetryLimit: An initial Path Message has reached its retry limit. - unableToRefresh: PRVT-RSVP has been unable to refresh an LSP. - resvErrTurnaround: PRVT-RSVP has received a ResvErr at the Egress node containing a REROUTING object and this is to be turned round into a PathErr. - incomingIfDown: The incoming MPLS data interface for an LSP has been deactivated. - outgoingIfDown: The outgoing MPLS data interface for an LSP has been deactivated.

prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRDecay.name: prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRDecay
prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRDecay.description: The percentage increase in the rapid retransmission interval for each consecutive unacknowledged RSVP Initial Path message. A value of 0 indicates a constant retransmission rate. A Path message is treated as an initial Path if it is the Path message which creates the LSP or a Path refresh message which requires re-routing.

prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRInterval.name: prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRInterval
prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRInterval.description: The rapid retransmission interval in milliseconds before an Initial Path message is first resent if no acknowledgement is received. A Path message is treated as an initial Path if it is the Path message which creates the LSP or a Path refresh message which requires re-routing.

prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRLimit.name: prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRLimit
prvtRsvpProductInitPathRRLimit.description: The maximum number of times an Initial Path message is resent if no acknowledgement is received. A Path message is treated as an initial Path if it is the Path message which creates the LSP or a Path refresh message which requires re-routing.

prvtRsvpProductEnableUni.name: prvtRsvpProductEnableUni
prvtRsvpProductEnableUni.description: A flag to indicate whether the local node supports UNI signaling messages.

prvtRsvpProductRestartCapable.name: prvtRsvpProductRestartCapable
prvtRsvpProductRestartCapable.description: A flag to indicate whether the local node should advertise itself as restart capable. This should be set to true if fault-tolerance is enabled in PRVT-MPLS or if the node supports recovery procedures.

prvtRsvpProductRestartTime.name: prvtRsvpProductRestartTime
prvtRsvpProductRestartTime.description: The time in milliseconds that the local node takes to restart RSVP-TE and the communication channel used for RSVP communication. This is advertised to neighbors in the Restart_Cap object in Hello messages. The value chosen should be large enough for RSVP to be terminated and restarted. If fault-tolerance is enabled in PRVT-MPLS, then sufficient time should be allowed for RSVP to fail over, which should include the time taken for the audit phase to complete. A value of 0xFFFFFFFF may be configured to imply an infinite restart time. Only used if prvtRsvpProductRestartCapable is set to true. Note that the maximum real time value that can be set is 0x7FFFFFFF. If a value is requested greater than 0x7FFFFFFF and less than 0xFFFFFFFF the request will be rejected.

prvtRsvpProductRecoveryTime.name: prvtRsvpProductRecoveryTime
prvtRsvpProductRecoveryTime.description: The period of time in milliseconds that the local node would like neighbors to take to resyncronize RSVP and MPLS forwarding information after the re-establishment of Hello connectivity. This is advertised to neighbors in the Restart_Cap object in Hello messages. A value of zero indicates that the node does not support resynchronization following failure of the local node. A value of 0xFFFFFFFF indicates an infinite recovery time. Note that if fault-tolerance is not enabled in PRVT-MPLS and the node is acting as an ingress for tunnels, then any ingress tunnels that need to be recovered should be configured during this recovery period. These tunnels should be configured in TE-MIB with the admin_status set to UP, otherwise they will be lost from the switch controller. Only used if prvtRsvpProductRestartCapable is set to true. Note that the maximum real time value that can be set is 0x7FFFFFFF. If a value is requested greater than 0x7FFFFFFF and less than 0xFFFFFFFF the request will be rejected.

prvtRsvpProductMinPeerRestart.name: prvtRsvpProductMinPeerRestart
prvtRsvpProductMinPeerRestart.description: The mininum period of time in milliseconds that RSVP should wait for a restart capable neighbor to regain Hello connectivity before invoking procedures related to communication loss. RSVP will wait for the maximum of this time and the restart_time advertised in the RESTART_CAP object in Hello messages from the neighbor.

prvtRsvpProductGracefulDelTimeout.name: prvtRsvpProductGracefulDelTimeout
prvtRsvpProductGracefulDelTimeout.description: The time in milliseconds that PRVT-MPLS will wait for graceful deletion to complete before the forced deletion procedure is used instead.

prvtRsvpProductEgressDelBehavior.name: prvtRsvpProductEgressDelBehavior
prvtRsvpProductEgressDelBehavior.description: Specifies the action that an egress node should take in the graceful deletion procedure on receipt of a Path message containing an Admin Status object with the D and R bits set. The possible values are:- - delWithPathErr: Send a PathErr message with the Path_State_removed flag set. - delWithResvD: Send a Resv message containing an Admin Status object with the D bit set.

prvtRsvpProductEnabUniConnSplicing.name: prvtRsvpProductEnabUniConnSplicing
prvtRsvpProductEnabUniConnSplicing.description: A flag to indicate whether UNI-N nodes should allow the splicing of UNI connections with proprietary ON connections.

prvtRsvpProductFastRerouteCaps.name: prvtRsvpProductFastRerouteCaps
prvtRsvpProductFastRerouteCaps.description: Specifies what fast reroute capabilities are enabled on this node. This field is only valid if the fast reroute extension is enabled in the prvtRsvpProductProtocolExtensions field above. - PLR: Node provides fast reroute point of local repair capability. - MP: Node provides fast reroute merge point capability. - DetourRestart: Node implements some protocol extensions to recover detour fast reroute LSPs after a node restart or an adjacent node restart. This flag is only valid if detourFastReroute flag is set in the prvtRsvpProductProtocolExtensions field above. Note that a node can still perform some FRR processing even if the PLR and MP flags are clear (at a detour transit for instance).

prvtRsvpProductFastRroutBkpRtryInt.name: prvtRsvpProductFastRroutBkpRtryInt
prvtRsvpProductFastRroutBkpRtryInt.description: When this node is a PLR, this field specifies the period that the node should wait before retrying the setup of a backup LSP which failed last time because no route was available. In the case that a backup LSP is set up but an error is received from upstream, setup will be attempted again immediately. This field is only valid if this node is defined as PLR capable in the _prvtRsvpProductFastRerouteCapabilities_ field above.

prvtRsvpProductErrorActionFlags.name: prvtRsvpProductErrorActionFlags
prvtRsvpProductErrorActionFlags.description: This field is used by PRVT-RSVP to determine whether it should take any special action following certain types of local errors. Each bit of this flags field corresponds to an error and a corresponding action. When one of these errors occurs, the relevant bit flag is checked - if set, the specified action is taken; if not set, the normal action is taken according the RSVP protocol. The possible bit values are the following. - eafTearStateOnLSIErr: When PRVT-RSVP receives a negative response to an ATG_LDB_CONNECT_LSP_XC message on a UNI node, the Path state is torn down.

prvtRsvpProductEnableNni.name: prvtRsvpProductEnableNni
prvtRsvpProductEnableNni.description: A flag to indicate whether the local node supports NNI signaling messages.

prvtRsvpProductBehaviorFlags.name: prvtRsvpProductBehaviorFlags
prvtRsvpProductBehaviorFlags.description: Specifies some detailed aspects of the behavior of PRVT-RSVP. This field may be changed while _admin_status_ is up. - enableTTLMatch: Whether to discard received RSVP packets sent with the Router Alert option if the IP and RSVP TTL values do not match. In certain circumstances TTL comparison can identify RSVP service breaks, and allow the discarding of packets that would otherwise disrupt installed LSPs. This option has no effect for Out Of Band operation. This option should be left disabled for LSP hierarchy operation (LSPs set up over existing LSPs) and for Facility Fast Reroute (which sets up backup LSPs over existing bypass LSPs).

prvtRsvpProductLabelSetStyle.name: prvtRsvpProductLabelSetStyle
prvtRsvpProductLabelSetStyle.description: Specifies the style of LABEL_SET object that should be used. RFCs 3741 and 3743 are unclear whether the LABEL_SET object should include LABEL headers. The correct interpretation is that the header should not be present, but there are implementations that include the LABEL header, so this option is included for compatibility with these implementations. - excludeLabelHeader: The LABEL_SET object contains concatenated LABEL values without the object headers. - includeLabelHeader: The LABEL_SET object contains concatenated LABEL objects with the object headers.

prvtRsvpProductLabelSetOperStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductLabelSetOperStatus
prvtRsvpProductLabelSetOperStatus.description: The current operational state of Label Set style. - excludeLabelHeader: The LABEL_SET object contains concatenated LABEL values without the object headers. - includeLabelHeader: The LABEL_SET object contains concatenated LABEL objects with the object headers. - goingToExclude: The Label Set Style is being changed from includeLabelHeader to excludeLabelHeader. - goingToInclude: The Label Set Style is being changed from excludeLabelHeader to includeLabelHeader.

prvtRsvpProductLabelSetTrapEnable.name: prvtRsvpProductLabelSetTrapEnable
prvtRsvpProductLabelSetTrapEnable.description: This object is used to enable traps for the Label Set style oper_status object.

prvtRsvpProductLabelSetChngAct.name: prvtRsvpProductLabelSetChngAct
prvtRsvpProductLabelSetChngAct.description: Specifies the action to take when the value of prvtRsvpProductLabelSetStyle is changed. - leaveLSPs: All nodes should suppress refreshes and switch to the new format while refreshes are suppressed. - tearLSPs: Any LSPs using label sets will be deleted before switching all nodes to the new format, and any new LSPs using label sets will be dropped/rejected until the switch is complete.

prvtRsvpProductExtPrtAdminStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductExtPrtAdminStatus
prvtRsvpProductExtPrtAdminStatus.description: The desired operational state of support for the extended PROTECTION object defined in draft-lang-ccamp-gmpls-recovery-e2e-signaling.

prvtRsvpProductUniIncSonetProfile.name: prvtRsvpProductUniIncSonetProfile
prvtRsvpProductUniIncSonetProfile.description: Specifies whether Sonet Profile is included on messages to or from a UNI-C node.

prvtRsvpProductFrrFacAdminStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductFrrFacAdminStatus
prvtRsvpProductFrrFacAdminStatus.description: Specifies whether backup LSPs can be put in place for LSPs requesting FRR using the facility method. Setting this to UP means that LSPs that request FRR using the facility method can have protection at this node. Existing LSPs that request FRR facility protection will have protection put in place when the next Path refresh is received. Setting this to DOWN means that LSPs that request FRR using the facility method will not be protected at this node. Existing LSPs that have FRR facility protection will lose that protection, and if the LSP had been rerouted to use the backup LSP then the protected LSP will be lost. This field replaces the bypassFastReroute flag on the protocol extensions field in this MIB (although the bypassFastReroute flag is still supported for backwards compatibility). It can be modified while RSVP is oper_status UP or DOWN. When this field is changed the bypassFastReroute flag is automatically modified to mirror the change.

prvtRsvpProductFrrFacOperStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductFrrFacOperStatus
prvtRsvpProductFrrFacOperStatus.description: The current operational status for FRR Facility support. When this is UP backup LSPs will be put in place, when this is down backup LSPs will not be put in place and there will be no LSPs that have backup LSPs.

prvtRsvpProductIpv6AdminStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductIpv6AdminStatus
prvtRsvpProductIpv6AdminStatus.description: Specifies whether the local node supports IPv6 LSPs. Setting this to UP means that this node supports IPv6 LSPs being set up to, from and through this node. Setting this to DOWN means that IPv6 LSPs are NOT supported by this node. Existing IPv6 LSPs for which this node is the ingress, egress or transit are torn down. This field can be modified while RSVP is oper_status UP or DOWN. The value of this field MUST match the value of the dcMplsTeMibRsvpIpv6AdminStatus field in the prvtMplsTeMibEntityTable.

prvtRsvpProductIpv6OperStatus.name: prvtRsvpProductIpv6OperStatus
prvtRsvpProductIpv6OperStatus.description: The current operational status for IPv6 support. When this is UP IPv6 LSPs can be set up to from or through this node. When this is down there will be no active IPv6 LSPs.

prvtRsvpProductAPIIpv6Address.name: prvtRsvpProductAPIIpv6Address
prvtRsvpProductAPIIpv6Address.description: Management assigned IPv6 address used to identify the (internal) LRAPI interface between RSVP and TE-MIB components. The configured API IPv6 address MUST not be a real address in the network. It is recommended that this is set to a non-zero reserved address value. This MUST be an address with global scope. If multi-stack support is set to PHOP, this address must be unique for each RSVP stack in the node. The same address(es) can be used on all nodes in the network.

prvtRsvpDiagnosticTable.name: prvtRsvpDiagnosticTable
prvtRsvpDiagnosticTable.description: The table of sessions that are being diagnosed.

prvtRsvpDiagnosticEntry.name: prvtRsvpDiagnosticEntry
prvtRsvpDiagnosticEntry.description: Each entry represents a session that is being diagnosed.

prvtRsvpDiagProductIndex.name: prvtRsvpDiagProductIndex
prvtRsvpDiagProductIndex.description: The index of the PRVT-RSVP product that is handling this query.

prvtRsvpDiagRequestIndex.name: prvtRsvpDiagRequestIndex
prvtRsvpDiagRequestIndex.description: The index of this prvtRsvpDiagnosticEntry. This corresponds to a particular session being diagnosed and is an arbitrary value, defined on row creation.

prvtRsvpDiagReqsInProgress.name: prvtRsvpDiagReqsInProgress
prvtRsvpDiagReqsInProgress.description: The number of outstanding diagnostic requests relating to this session.

prvtRsvpDiagSessionEndPoint.name: prvtRsvpDiagSessionEndPoint
prvtRsvpDiagSessionEndPoint.description: The IP address of the tunnel end point, from the LSP_TUNNEL_IPv4 session object.

prvtRsvpDiagSessionTunnelId.name: prvtRsvpDiagSessionTunnelId
prvtRsvpDiagSessionTunnelId.description: The tunnel ID, from the LSP_TUNNEL_IPv4 session object.

prvtRsvpDiagSessionExtTunnelId.name: prvtRsvpDiagSessionExtTunnelId
prvtRsvpDiagSessionExtTunnelId.description: The extended tunnel ID, from the LSP_TUNNEL_IPv4 session object.

prvtRsvpDiagLastHop.name: prvtRsvpDiagLastHop
prvtRsvpDiagLastHop.description: The IP address of the last hop to be queried. This is the address to which the DREQ message is first sent.

prvtRsvpDiagSender.name: prvtRsvpDiagSender
prvtRsvpDiagSender.description: The IP address of the sender for the specified session.

prvtRsvpDiagMaxHops.name: prvtRsvpDiagMaxHops
prvtRsvpDiagMaxHops.description: The maximum number of hops to diagnose.

prvtRsvpDiagHopByHopReply.name: prvtRsvpDiagHopByHopReply
prvtRsvpDiagHopByHopReply.description: A flag to indicate that DREPs should be returned hop-by- hop using the reverse of the path taken by the DREQ.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeTable.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeTable
prvtRsvpDiagNodeTable.description: The table of nodes within a session that is being diagnosed. External management can extract information from this table, but cannot modify information in it.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeEntry.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeEntry
prvtRsvpDiagNodeEntry.description: Each entry represents a node within a session that is being diagnosed.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeProductIndex.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeProductIndex
prvtRsvpDiagNodeProductIndex.description: The index of the PRVT-RSVP product that is handling this query.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeRequestIndex.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeRequestIndex
prvtRsvpDiagNodeRequestIndex.description: The index of the corresponding request in prvtRsvpDiagnosticTable.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeIndex.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeIndex
prvtRsvpDiagNodeIndex.description: The index of this prvtRsvpDiagNodeEntry. This is equivalent to the hop number, with 1 being the ingress.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeType.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeType
prvtRsvpDiagNodeType.description: The type of the node: ingress, transit, egress or missing. Missing indicates that no diagnostic response has been received for this node, and this entry may in fact represent more than one node.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeDreqArrivalTime.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeDreqArrivalTime
prvtRsvpDiagNodeDreqArrivalTime.description: The arrival time of the DREQ at the node, specified as a 32-bit NTP timestamp.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeIncomingIfAddr.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeIncomingIfAddr
prvtRsvpDiagNodeIncomingIfAddr.description: The IP address of the interface on which message from the sender are expected to arrive at this node, or 0 if unknown.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeOutgoingIfAddr.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeOutgoingIfAddr
prvtRsvpDiagNodeOutgoingIfAddr.description: The IP address of the interface through which the DREQ arrived and to which messages flow from the given sender for the specified session address, or 0 if unknown.

prvtRsvpDiagNodePrevHopAddr.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodePrevHopAddr
prvtRsvpDiagNodePrevHopAddr.description: The IP address from which this node receives RSVP PATH messages for this source, or 0 if unknown. This is also the address to which the DREQ was forwarded.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeDTTL.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeDTTL
prvtRsvpDiagNodeDTTL.description: The number of IP hops traversed by the DREQ between the downstream RSVP node and this node.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeMFlag.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeMFlag
prvtRsvpDiagNodeMFlag.description: A flag that indicates whether the reservation described by the response objects is merged with reservations from other downstream interfaces before being forwarded upstream.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeRErr.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeRErr
prvtRsvpDiagNodeRErr.description: The error conditions at this node. Bit 3 indicates ROUTE object too big; Bit 2 indicates packet too big; Bit 1 indicates no PATH state. Bit 1 is the least significant bit.

prvtRsvpDiagNodeTimerValue.name: prvtRsvpDiagNodeTimerValue
prvtRsvpDiagNodeTimerValue.description: The local refresh timer value in seconds.

prvtRsvpDiagRsvpHopAddr.name: prvtRsvpDiagRsvpHopAddr
prvtRsvpDiagRsvpHopAddr.description: The hop address from the session's RSVP_HOP object.

prvtRsvpDiagRsvpHopLIH.name: prvtRsvpDiagRsvpHopLIH
prvtRsvpDiagRsvpHopLIH.description: The LIH from the session's RSVP_HOP object.

prvtRsvpDiagSenderTpltAddress.name: prvtRsvpDiagSenderTpltAddress
prvtRsvpDiagSenderTpltAddress.description: The address from the session's SENDER_TEMPLATE object.

prvtRsvpDiagSenderTpltLSPId.name: prvtRsvpDiagSenderTpltLSPId
prvtRsvpDiagSenderTpltLSPId.description: The LSP ID from the session's SENDER_TEMPLATE object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLBktRate.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLBktRate
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLBktRate.description: Int-serv controlled load token bucket rate in bytes per second, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLBktDep.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLBktDep
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLBktDep.description: Int-serv controlled load token bucket depth in bytes, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLPkDataRate.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLPkDataRate
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLPkDataRate.description: Int-serv controlled load peak data rate in bytes per second, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLMinPolUnit.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLMinPolUnit
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLMinPolUnit.description: Int-serv controlled load minimum policed unit from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLMaxPktSize.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLMaxPktSize
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCLMaxPktSize.description: Int-serv controlled load maximum packet size from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQBktRate.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQBktRate
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQBktRate.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS token bucket rate in bytes per second, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQBktDep.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQBktDep
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQBktDep.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS token bucket depth in bytes, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQPkDataRate.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQPkDataRate
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQPkDataRate.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS peak data rate in bytes per second, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQMinPolUnit.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQMinPolUnit
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQMinPolUnit.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS minimum policed unit from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQMaxPktSize.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQMaxPktSize
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQMaxPktSize.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS maximum packet size from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQRate.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQRate
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQRate.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS rate in bytes per second, from the session's FLOWSPEC object. This value is rounded to the nearest integer.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQSlack.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQSlack
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecGQSlack.description: Int-serv guaranteed QoS slack in microseconds, from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCoSCoS.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCoSCoS
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCoSCoS.description: CoS class of service from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCoSMTU.name: prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCoSMTU
prvtRsvpDiagFlowSpecCoSMTU.description: CoS maximum packet size from the session's FLOWSPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFilterSpecAddress.name: prvtRsvpDiagFilterSpecAddress
prvtRsvpDiagFilterSpecAddress.description: The address from the session's FILTER_SPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagFilterSpecLSPId.name: prvtRsvpDiagFilterSpecLSPId
prvtRsvpDiagFilterSpecLSPId.description: The LSP ID from the session's FILTER_SPEC object.

prvtRsvpDiagConfirmRcvAddr.name: prvtRsvpDiagConfirmRcvAddr
prvtRsvpDiagConfirmRcvAddr.description: The address from the session's CONFIRM object.

prvtRsvpDiagStyle.name: prvtRsvpDiagStyle
prvtRsvpDiagStyle.description: The style word from the session's STYLE object.

prvtRsvpCompliance.name: prvtRsvpCompliance
prvtRsvpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the PRVT-RSVP product MIB.
